added.title: The Great Holiday Escape
added.description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: Gumbearable
added.description: After accidentally swallowing a piece of gum Owen has to protect his friends by jumping into gum volcano.

added.title: Whack Mirror
added.description: Chef warns Beth and Cody making goofy faces into a mirror will cause them to get stuck that way. It turns out he was right, just not in the way any of them ever imagined.

added.title: Broken Back Kotter
added.description: Izzy nominates Chef for the Daycare Professional of the Year award and will do whatever it takes to see him win. As it turns out, it takes a lot.

added.title: Weekend at Buddy's
added.description: After Cody's best friend doll breaks on their watch, Owen and Beth put themselves in grave danger while trying to do the right thing.

added.title: MacArthur Park
added.description: After losing countless jobs because of the kids, MacArthur shows up at the school seeking revenge.

added.title: Double Hex
added.description: While bird watching at Pinnacles National Park, Gwen and Ben get into a competition of who can spot more birds first, but once a forest fire interrupts their fun, Team Tennyson must hurry if they are to save the bird population and discover who is behind the suspiciously growing fire: Hex!

added.title: Ye Olde Laser Duel
added.description: As team Tennyson admires the efficiency of a super modern train station, Ben is quick to sniff out one of Steam Smythe's robots holding up the line. Once the fed up villain tricks our hero into accepting a duel, the fate of the Omnitrix hangs in the balance and it's up to Ben to set things right.

added.title: Ben Again and Again
added.description: After Billy Billions' efforts to carve his face onto Mount Rushmore with a laser are thwarted by Ben, the billionaire brat turns his focus on removing Ben from the Omnitrix, but once he accidentally rips open a rift in space-time, the two must carefully navigate another timeline if they are to return to the present.

added.title: Vote Zombozo!
added.description: When the Rustbucket must tune-up in the same town as Zombozo's latest campaign trail stop, Ben soon discovers the clown is using his speeches to hypnotize then rob the town, and Team Tennyson must stop the baddie from winning the election.

added.title: Drone On
added.description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

added.title: And Then There Were 10
added.description: Ben discovers the Omnitrix, and when it attaches itself to Ben's wrist, he discovers it allows him to become any one of ten alien heroes.

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Permanent Retirement
added.description: Grandpa, Gwen and Ben visit an old maid relative only to find that her retirement community has been overtaken by a shapeshifting aliens called Limax.

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Clyde Five
added.description: Ben's country cousin wants to be a hero, too.

added.title: Rook Tales
added.description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

added.title: Charm School
added.description: At Gwen's college, Ben suspects a new teacher and new student are old enemies.

added.title: The Ballad of Mr. Baumann
added.description: The grouchy storekeeper has a big secret, and she's not of this Earth.

added.title: Fight at the Museum
added.description: Alien artifacts in Bellwood attract enemies from the future and friends from the past.

added.title: Field Trip
added.description: A group of teenage superheroes are being shown around the Fortress of Solitude when they inadvertently cause the phantom zone projector to trap Superman and release three Kryptonian criminals.

added.title: Rage of the Red Lanterns
added.description: Chased by the Red Lanterns, Lobo seeks sanctuary with the Justice League. As the League attempts to stave off the Red Lanterns, Lobo reveals the real reason he wants shelter in the Watchtower, he wants access to a powerful space weapon being held by our heroes.

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: Inside Job
added.description: In a "Fantastic Voyage" like adventure, Atom shrinks Batman and Wonder Woman so they can enter Superman's bloodstream and destroy a lethal nanite virus.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: Champion of the Universe, Dan!/Operation Babysitter
added.description: Champion of the Universe, Dan!: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all./Operation Babysitter: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

added.title: Beastie Team Battle/Ajit and Lia
added.description: Beastie Team Battle: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend./Ajit and Lia: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

added.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
added.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

added.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
added.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

added.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
added.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: Vote Por Zombozo
added.description: Cuando el Chatarra debe ponerse a punto en la misma ciudad por donde pasa la campaña de Zombozo, Ben pronto descubre que el payaso usa sus discursos para hipnotizar al pueblo y robarse sus pertenencias. El equipo Tennyson debe impedir que el villano gane las elecciones.

added.title: Vuela Dron
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enfrentan en una guerra de avioncitos de papel sumamente competitiva. Pero cuando unos drones con tecnología alienígena bombardean el Rustbucket, los primos deben trabajar juntos para derribar el ataque aéreo y descubrir quién está detrás de eso: iVilgax, el conquistador extraterrestre!

added.title: Los Safaris son Malos
added.description: En su paseo a Adrenaworld West, Ben toma un desvío por una selva y descubre que lo persigue el malvado Tim Buktu. iNuestro héroe debe ser más listo que el villano si quiere llegar al parque de diversiones con vida!

added.title: La Naturaleza de las Cosas
added.description: Mientras pasean por el Parque Nacional Geyser Gulch, el trío Tennyson descubre un generador a vapor de Steam Smyth y debe apagarlo antes de que sobrecargue la red eléctrica o, peor, icause un terremoto masivo que destruya el parque entero!

added.title: Ruidosos y Peludos
added.description: Cuando los Tennyson se van del Festival Frozen Man, Lord Decibel ocupa el escenario central para amenazar a los asistentes y crear una avalancha si no pagan el rescate que pide. iBen se ve superado por su rival y debe salir de su zona de confort para salvar al festival de su entrometido enemigo!

added.title: Brand New Track
added.description: Thomas and Percy explore a brand-new track the evening before the route is opened. Everything seems new and exciting, and even a night spent stuck in the mud turns into a wonderful experience. Only in the light of day do they realize that nothing they saw was really "new" at all - it just seemed so because they brought to it a sense of delight and discovery.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Stink Monster
added.description: Thomas and the other young engines encounter a stink monster that threatens to spread a stench all over Knapford! When Percy is kidnapped by the stink monster, the rest of the Biggest Adventure Club band together to create a plan to save their friend and stop the stink monster in its tracks! Looking closer, they realize it's their good friend Whiff's new invention causing a stink!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Festival of Hearts
added.description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

added.title: An Almost Eggless Easter
added.description: When the Easter Bunny's beautifully-painted eggs are drained of their color, it looks like Dibble will miss her first Easter egg hunt - she's really been looking forward to it. The Bears must find a way to repaint all the eggs before the big day.

added.title: A Wish-Full Reunion
added.description: Mysterious flying hearts appear in Care-A-Lot and bring Wish Bear to the Silver Lining. She joins the Care Bears on a mission to bring a mystical mother bird's missing baby chicks home, and give a new home to an orphan bird.

added.title: The Birthday That Wasn't
added.description: Dibble misunderstands the Bears' intentions when they secretly make a plush toy Whiffle for her "Un-birthday." Thinking it's real and that the Bears love it more than they love her, she steals it and plans to leave it in the forest. She has second thoughts and returns her "rival" to her friends, only to learn that it's a gift to show their love for her.

added.title: The Big Rumble
added.description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

added.title: Mr. McStuffles
added.description: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it.

added.title: Picture This!
added.description: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups
added.description: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut.

added.title: A Clean Sweep
added.description: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!
added.description: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying.
